06:58.270 --> 06:59.930
Trust me.

07:03.590 --> 07:05.180
But guess what, though.

07:06.210 --> 07:07.680
I love you.

07:07.880 --> 07:09.620
Prove it. Mmm.

07:09.820 --> 07:11.600
[both laugh]

07:18.780 --> 07:21.660
<i>LIKEM:</i>
<i>Foreigners from North Africa</i>
<i>and Europe</i>

07:21.860 --> 07:25.700
started buying our people
many centuries ago.

07:25.900 --> 07:30.400
The foreigners bought
Black souls from Black traders

07:30.600 --> 07:35.820
representing the holy Songhai,
Ashanti, and Benin Empires.

07:36.020 --> 07:38.990
That was a result of tribalism.

07:39.190 --> 07:41.910
After a war the winners sold

07:42.110 --> 07:44.630
the losers into servitude.

07:45.770 --> 07:48.830
This practice continued
for centuries.

07:49.030 --> 07:52.260
It was accepted,
it was a part of life,

07:52.460 --> 07:57.910
but things changed when
foreigners bought our people,

07:58.110 --> 08:02.070
and after that they were gone
as if they had never been.

08:02.270 --> 08:05.090
Daughters and sons not dead

08:05.290 --> 08:09.990
so they could be buried
and eulogized.

08:10.190 --> 08:11.800
[sighs]

08:12.000 --> 08:16.460
Much later we learned
that our women were...

08:16.660 --> 08:18.690
raped and defiled.

08:18.890 --> 08:23.330
Young mothers drowned themselves
and their babies.

08:23.530 --> 08:28.560
Brokenhearted men and women
died from typhus,

08:28.760 --> 08:31.960
their wills and bodies
shattered.

08:32.160 --> 08:35.910
Nearly two million souls
perished

08:36.110 --> 08:38.600
on the Middle Passage
from the motherland

08:38.800 --> 08:40.620
to hell.

08:56.220 --> 08:58.850
<i>Those that survived</i>

08:59.050 --> 09:01.940
<i>could not remember</i>
<i>their names...</i>

09:02.140 --> 09:03.970
<i>[woman screaming]</i>

09:04.170 --> 09:06.080
<i>...their gods, languages,</i>

09:06.280 --> 09:07.940
<i>and their people.</i>

09:08.140 --> 09:10.080
<i>[chains rattling]</i>

09:10.280 --> 09:13.690
<i>[women crying]</i>

09:13.890 --> 09:16.070
<i>And we did not think about the.</i>

09:17.660 --> 09:20.920
They were souls lost on us.

09:21.120 --> 09:22.960
So we keep that door...

09:23.160 --> 09:26.040
<i>[overlapping screaming]</i>

09:32.600 --> 09:35.110
<i>...to remind us of the sins</i>

09:35.310 --> 09:37.920
against the children
of Africa...

09:40.680 --> 09:42.680
<i>...to remind us...</i>

09:44.540 --> 09:46.580
<i>...of our bargain...</i>

09:49.100 --> 09:51.100
<i>...with the devil.</i>

10:09.220 --> 10:12.090
<i>LEON:</i>
<i>That was Black people</i>
<i>selling they own brothers.</i>

10:14.260 --> 10:16.780
<i>WANDA:</i>
<i>They weren't alone, though.</i>

10:20.410 --> 10:24.450
At least...
they forgave themselves.

10:25.650 --> 10:28.210
Vowed to never do it again.

10:30.660 --> 10:32.940
But they did it,
and it was over with.

10:34.910 --> 10:37.380
And here I am.

10:37.580 --> 10:40.500
I was doing the same thing
less than a month ago.

10:41.840 --> 10:44.330
You ain't never sold
your people into slavery.

10:46.160 --> 10:47.750
I sold 'em crack.

10:49.610 --> 10:52.060
I wrapped them chains
around their necks.

10:57.510 --> 11:00.330
Sometimes I think it's...

11:00.530 --> 11:03.170
easier to escape slavery than...

11:04.870 --> 11:07.080
...to escape crack.

11:07.280 --> 11:08.730
How so?

11:16.220 --> 11:19.260
If you gave a slave
an opportunity for freedom...

11:22.710 --> 11:24.820
...they'll take that
and never look back.

11:26.890 --> 11:29.860
If you gave the same opportunity
to a crackhead...

11:31.790 --> 11:33.690
...they may always look back.

11:39.490 --> 11:41.390
[cries]

11:54.500 --> 11:56.160
Fuck.

12:08.580 --> 12:10.660
[bird chittering]

12:14.690 --> 12:17.250
I got to get free
from America, Lee.

12:18.700 --> 12:20.790
