23:52.390 --> 23:55.190
[woman moaning]

23:55.390 --> 23:56.880
Hey, what's happening?

23:57.980 --> 24:00.230
DEON:
Huh. What's up, Lee?

24:03.090 --> 24:04.670
Fuck!

24:04.870 --> 24:06.980
[sighs]

24:07.180 --> 24:08.980
Look at you.

24:09.180 --> 24:11.190
Back from the
motherfucking motherland.

24:11.390 --> 24:12.900
Power to the people, my nigga.

24:13.100 --> 24:14.280
[laughs]

24:16.450 --> 24:18.990
What's all this shit going on?

24:19.190 --> 24:20.250
You and Jerome

24:20.450 --> 24:22.130
and that cop
fucking with Franklin?

24:22.330 --> 24:24.030
He the nigga fucking with me.

24:24.230 --> 24:25.340
Nigga tried to kill me.

24:25.540 --> 24:27.080
Why?

24:27.290 --> 24:28.260
I don't know.

24:28.460 --> 24:30.660
Nigga crazy, that's all.

24:30.860 --> 24:32.430
Nigga done lost
his motherfucking mind.

24:32.640 --> 24:33.830
He see all this
bread I'm getting,

24:34.030 --> 24:35.470
and he want a little piece.

24:36.750 --> 24:38.060
Franklin don't need
what you got.

24:38.260 --> 24:40.150
He make his own money.

24:40.350 --> 24:42.760
He used to make his own money.

24:42.960 --> 24:44.270
Yeah, you've been gone
a little while, homie.

24:44.470 --> 24:46.620
Word on the street is
he lost what he made.

24:46.820 --> 24:48.590
That's why he hit
his own uncle's warehouse.

24:50.860 --> 24:53.420
What that got to do with you?

24:53.620 --> 24:56.080
Not a damn thing.

24:58.530 --> 25:01.120
Einstein says you staying
at your old place.

25:01.320 --> 25:03.360
It's the only place I got.

25:04.840 --> 25:07.380
So, what, you trying
to come back

25:07.580 --> 25:09.090
and work for me?

25:09.290 --> 25:10.900
♪ <i>Switch the mix, Mr. DJ</i>♪

25:11.100 --> 25:12.600
♪ <i>Play that beat, why don't</i>
<i>you play it for me?</i>♪

25:12.800 --> 25:13.600
Nah, I'm good.

25:13.800 --> 25:15.340
♪ <i>Switch the mix, Mr. DJ</i>♪

25:15.540 --> 25:17.290
♪ <i>Play that beat, why don't</i>
<i>you play it for me?</i>♪

25:17.490 --> 25:19.830
As long as you stay in
your lane, we cool, bro.

25:20.030 --> 25:22.190
♪ <i>Why don't you</i>
<i>play it for me?</i>♪

25:22.390 --> 25:23.610
♪ <i>Switch the mix, Mr. DJ</i>♪

25:23.810 --> 25:24.920
♪ <i>Play that beat</i>♪

25:25.120 --> 25:26.690
♪ <i>Play that beat.</i>♪

25:28.180 --> 25:30.040
The Mexican going with you?

25:36.940 --> 25:38.950
Good.

25:40.360 --> 25:42.250
The team meeting you
down there are mercs.

25:42.450 --> 25:44.990
They like killing.

25:45.190 --> 25:46.630
But if that attack comes,

25:46.830 --> 25:49.030
you'll need to take one
of these guys alive.

25:54.170 --> 25:55.520
- Yeah. I know.
- [dry fires rifle]

25:55.720 --> 25:57.310
[coin drops]

25:57.510 --> 25:59.090
[line ringing]

25:59.290 --> 26:02.040
- We need to talk. Now.
<i>- TONY: Okay,</i>

26:02.240 --> 26:04.180
<i>let's meet at the usual place.</i>

26:04.380 --> 26:06.040
Okay, see you there.

26:11.530 --> 26:14.660
Something about Avi's
last shipment of arms,

26:14.860 --> 26:15.850
that it might be hit.

26:16.050 --> 26:17.710
Where do you leave from,
where do you land?

26:17.910 --> 26:20.940
I already told you,
I don't know.

26:21.140 --> 26:23.670
I can't help you if
I don't know what's going on.

26:23.870 --> 26:27.430
And I can't tell you
what I do not know, <i>cabrón.</i>

26:27.630 --> 26:29.240
Now that we have

26:29.440 --> 26:30.950
the photographs of Louie
doing the drop,

26:31.150 --> 26:32.610
we're going to want to move
on Teddy's warehouse

26:32.810 --> 26:33.850
in the next few days,

26:34.050 --> 26:35.640
so make sure you make it back

26:35.840 --> 26:37.940
from Costa Rica, you hear me?

26:40.080 --> 26:42.390
[camera shutter clicking]

26:44.600 --> 26:46.600
[car doors closing]

26:59.720 --> 27:03.240
TEDDY:
Relax. Wheels down
in 20 minutes.

27:12.630 --> 27:14.040
Yeah.

27:27.990 --> 27:29.440
You Ramos?

27:29.640 --> 27:30.840
<i>Sí.</i>

27:31.040 --> 27:32.920
Teddy. That's Gustavo.

27:35.100 --> 27:37.930
The port at Golfito.

27:41.280 --> 27:44.110
Where at 1400 hours,
a shipment of cargo

27:44.310 --> 27:45.680
will be arrive and be offloaded

27:45.880 --> 27:47.200
onto third-party transports.

27:47.400 --> 27:50.600
[speaks Spanish]

27:50.800 --> 27:52.580
TEDDY:
Our objective is to
secure that cargo,

27:52.780 --> 27:55.260
and, if attacked, identify
the responsible parties.

27:55.460 --> 27:59.160
[speaks Spanish]

27:59.360 --> 28:01.420
There'll be three teams:
Alpha, Bravo, Charlie.

28:01.620 --> 28:03.730
[speaks Spanish]

28:03.930 --> 28:05.300
Three locations, you'll
see them marked there.

28:05.500 --> 28:07.220
[speaks Spanish]

28:07.420 --> 28:08.960
He and I will be Delta.
We'll be in the tower.

28:09.160 --> 28:11.950
[speaks Spanish]

28:12.150 --> 28:13.090
TEDDY:
If the hostiles do arrive,

28:13.290 --> 28:15.050
you'll stay hidden,

28:15.250 --> 28:16.260
you'll wait for our signal,

28:16.460 --> 28:19.270
then you'll engage
and eliminate the threat.

28:19.460 --> 28:21.320
[speaks Spanish]

28:21.520 --> 28:22.790
TEDDY:
Once the location's secure,

28:22.990 --> 28:25.370
I need every member of
the assaulting party searched,

28:25.570 --> 28:27.620
and their gear confiscated.

28:27.820 --> 28:29.620
[speaks Spanish]

28:29.820 --> 28:31.900
I'm not talking about
being patted down,

28:32.100 --> 28:33.560
I'm saying if they've got
intel in their goddamn socks,

28:33.750 --> 28:35.230
I need it found, you understand?

28:36.400 --> 28:39.570
[speaks Spanish]

28:42.790 --> 28:46.030
Securing the cargo and not
finding out who came after it

28:46.230 --> 28:48.400
will be considered
a mission failure.

28:48.600 --> 28:50.650
[speaks Spanish]

28:52.040 --> 28:53.490
Any questions?

28:53.690 --> 28:54.580
Yes.

28:54.780 --> 28:57.560
What's the signal?

29:11.750 --> 29:13.750
[dogs barking in distance]

29:23.270 --> 29:24.830
Hey, Grandma.

29:27.800 --> 29:29.270
Wanda?

29:29.470 --> 29:30.990
WANDA:
You look good.

29:31.190 --> 29:33.340
Uh-huh. Thank you.

29:33.540 --> 29:35.530
- Can I come in?
- Uh-uh.

29:35.730 --> 29:37.290
What do you want?

29:39.080 --> 29:41.570
I brought you
a present from Africa.

29:41.770 --> 29:43.090
Where are my
rose-colored pearls?

29:43.290 --> 29:46.270
I don't know, that was
a long time ago, Grandma.

29:46.470 --> 29:48.750
When I was on the rock.
I gave that up.

29:48.950 --> 29:49.890
Like you did them pearls?

29:50.090 --> 29:53.550
[sighs] I'm sorry. But...

29:53.750 --> 29:56.030
I brought you a necklace
from Ghana.

29:58.270 --> 30:00.070
What the fuck you want?

30:00.270 --> 30:02.640
I miss you.

30:02.840 --> 30:04.560
You should have
thought about that

30:04.760 --> 30:06.390
before you robbed me

30:06.590 --> 30:08.030
and hit me

30:08.230 --> 30:11.390
and cursed me before God.

30:11.590 --> 30:13.260
That's a nice dress you got on,

30:13.460 --> 30:14.950
but I bet you

30:15.150 --> 30:17.490
dollars to donuts that
they's got blood on the hem.

30:17.690 --> 30:20.260
Can I at least leave my gift?

30:21.260 --> 30:22.610
I'm going to close this door,

30:22.810 --> 30:24.670
and if you want to
leave it on the knob,

30:24.870 --> 30:26.230
you can do that.

30:29.860 --> 30:31.310
[gasps]

30:34.310 --> 30:35.830
[shudders]

30:47.050 --> 30:48.530
[crying]

30:54.190 --> 30:55.940
<i>NEWSWOMAN [over radio]: Police</i>
<i>say it's the love of drugs</i>

30:56.140 --> 30:58.640
<i>and money that keeps the</i>
<i>death toll high and climbing.</i>

31:06.650 --> 31:08.000
Hey.

31:09.170 --> 31:10.920
This is a good moment.

31:11.120 --> 31:12.450
Enjoy it.

31:25.020 --> 31:27.670
[quiet chatter]

31:39.550 --> 31:41.040
I didn't think she was coming.

31:41.240 --> 31:42.480
Yeah, me neither.

31:44.040 --> 31:45.520
Hey, Mama.

31:46.730 --> 31:48.870
- Hi, baby.
- Hi.

31:49.070 --> 31:50.590
Hi, baby.

31:54.420 --> 31:55.870
Thanks for coming.

31:59.430 --> 32:01.540
There it is.

32:01.740 --> 32:04.230
Everything you've
been fighting for.

32:06.200 --> 32:07.710
Uh-huh.

32:17.930 --> 32:19.930
[engine turns off]

32:37.430 --> 32:39.190
It's for Jerome and Louie.

33:05.670 --> 33:07.050
[grunts softly]

33:19.650 --> 33:21.100
I appreciate y'all seeing me.

33:22.170 --> 33:24.400
That's all right. Welcome home.

33:24.600 --> 33:26.490
Brought you something.

33:26.690 --> 33:28.260
Your man outside opened it.

33:28.460 --> 33:30.770
Guess he thought I was bringing
y'all a bomb or something.

33:30.970 --> 33:32.580
It's a wedding gift.

33:32.780 --> 33:34.890
Aw, you got us a wedding gift?

33:35.090 --> 33:37.320
Yeah, I figured better
late than never.

33:38.670 --> 33:40.640
When a member
of a tribe travels,

33:40.840 --> 33:42.290
they use this as they passport.

33:42.490 --> 33:44.560
The man who gave me this
said it belonged to a chief,

33:44.760 --> 33:46.300
and that was his wife's face,

33:46.500 --> 33:48.470
so it just
made me think of y'all.

33:48.670 --> 33:50.700
Thank you, Leon.

33:50.900 --> 33:52.510
You're welcome.

33:52.710 --> 33:54.310
JEROME:
It must be nice,

33:54.510 --> 33:55.880
you run off to Africa.

33:56.080 --> 33:59.610
Come back, wave that
shit in our face, right?

33:59.800 --> 34:01.350
No, I-I came back to talk,

34:01.550 --> 34:03.800
and I don't think you want
to hear what I got to say.

34:04.000 --> 34:05.150
Don't say it, nigga.

34:05.350 --> 34:06.920
Jerome, if you was in my
shoes, what would you do?

34:07.120 --> 34:08.670
I can't just sit back
and let this shit happen.

34:08.870 --> 34:10.150
Sure, you can.

34:10.350 --> 34:11.760
That's the easiest
shit in the world.

34:11.950 --> 34:13.390
Okay, well,
it ain't easy for me.

34:15.050 --> 34:16.570
Why is that?

34:18.050 --> 34:20.880
Fuck, you high and mighty now.

34:22.160 --> 34:23.770
LOUIE:
You see them bullets
out there, Leon?

34:23.970 --> 34:26.150
They came at us here.

34:26.350 --> 34:29.380
Then they came at us at our
hotel on our fucking honeymoon.

34:29.580 --> 34:32.120
And when Jerome extended
his hand, Franklin bit it.

34:32.320 --> 34:34.330
Okay, I understand that,
but if you kill Franklin,

34:34.530 --> 34:35.810
or Franklin kill you,

34:36.010 --> 34:37.950
that'll destroy Cissy and
the whole fucking family.

34:38.150 --> 34:40.090
JEROME:
The fuck it got to do with you?

34:40.290 --> 34:42.250
You ain't family.

34:43.280 --> 34:45.700
What you mean by that?

34:45.900 --> 34:47.310
JEROME:
You know what the fuck
I mean by that.

34:47.510 --> 34:49.710
Franklin used you.

34:49.910 --> 34:52.680
He used you the same way
that he used us.

34:52.880 --> 34:55.330
Got you out here
catching bodies.

34:56.430 --> 34:58.030
And then, 'cause you
killed a goddamn kid,

34:58.230 --> 35:00.580
now you see the light, nigga?

35:02.100 --> 35:04.070
And now you come here and what?

35:04.270 --> 35:06.290
You want to make peace?

35:06.490 --> 35:07.930
Right?

35:09.240 --> 35:11.410
Forgive and forget?

35:14.490 --> 35:16.520
Get the fuck out of here,
little nigga.

35:18.320 --> 35:20.080
Take that dumb shit with you.

35:21.080 --> 35:23.120
This is yours, you can do
whatever you want with it.

35:37.650 --> 35:40.050
[indistinct radio chatter
in Spanish]

35:40.250 --> 35:43.310
[seabirds squawking]

35:58.010 --> 36:00.150
GUSTAVO:
How long do we wait?

36:04.260 --> 36:05.680
Why, you got
somewhere else to be?

36:13.170 --> 36:14.440
TEDDY:
You all right?

36:16.450 --> 36:19.520
Been reading the papers
about this war.

36:20.730 --> 36:22.450
Some say it will end soon...

36:24.110 --> 36:25.840
...and your side will win.

36:26.040 --> 36:29.200
You guys have the expression,
"Don't count your chickens"?

36:29.400 --> 36:32.190
Yeah... <i>No cantes victoria.</i>

36:33.700 --> 36:35.530
But it gonna end, right?

36:37.360 --> 36:39.050
Yeah, someday it will.

36:40.300 --> 36:42.300
And then what happens
to you and me?

36:48.030 --> 36:50.090
Reckon I'll go my way,
you go yours.

36:50.290 --> 36:52.860
<i>Así nomás.</i>

37:02.390 --> 37:03.550
[clucks tongue]

37:03.750 --> 37:05.080
Green light.

37:12.430 --> 37:14.190
[shouting in Spanish]

37:27.070 --> 37:29.590
[speaking Spanish]

37:34.800 --> 37:38.050
[both speaking Spanish]

37:38.250 --> 37:39.770
[gunshots]

37:50.300 --> 37:51.610
You good?

37:59.960 --> 38:01.540
Who sent you?

38:01.740 --> 38:03.620
<i>Tu puta madre gringo.</i>

38:08.940 --> 38:10.130
All right,
collect everything you can.

38:10.330 --> 38:11.680
Five minutes, we're out of here.

38:11.880 --> 38:14.110
<i> ¡Cinco minutos!</i>
<i> ¡Vamos, vamos, vamos!</i>

38:23.640 --> 38:26.090
Goddamn...

38:58.710 --> 39:01.090
What are you hoping to find?

39:14.620 --> 39:17.210
<i>No mames.</i>

39:46.000 --> 39:49.180
Now what? What does it say?

39:49.380 --> 39:51.010
- TEDDY: I don't know.
- You don't know?

39:51.210 --> 39:53.080
I know who wrote it.

39:54.590 --> 39:56.620
The Russians.

39:56.820 --> 39:58.360
GUSTAVO:
The Russians?

40:01.910 --> 40:04.490
Tried to blow up this operation.

40:04.690 --> 40:06.680
<i>[knock on door]</i>

40:09.230 --> 40:11.200
Sup, Lee?

40:11.400 --> 40:13.200
What's up?

40:13.400 --> 40:15.060
Come on in.

40:18.550 --> 40:20.210
What the fuck happened here?

40:22.040 --> 40:23.690
Jerome and fuckin' Louie.

40:24.800 --> 40:28.100
Sent dirty cops here
to search the place.

40:28.300 --> 40:30.080
Had a warrant and everything.

40:30.280 --> 40:32.450
But you don't keep
nothin' here, though.

40:32.650 --> 40:34.600
And they weren't
looking for nothing.

40:36.950 --> 40:38.430
You gonna leave?

40:39.950 --> 40:41.920
When I'm good and ready.

40:44.230 --> 40:46.030
Shit, um...

40:46.230 --> 40:47.750
I got burgers, nigga.

40:51.370 --> 40:53.580
FRANKLIN:
Wish you was back there by now?

40:55.240 --> 40:57.070
It was so different.

40:58.070 --> 40:59.940
Couple weeks in,

41:00.140 --> 41:02.030
all of this shit
started to fade.

41:02.230 --> 41:03.370
FRANKLIN:
Hmm.

41:03.570 --> 41:05.860
Kev, Tianna,

41:06.060 --> 41:08.150
money, rock...

41:09.290 --> 41:10.730
But, the end of the day,

41:10.930 --> 41:13.120
being gone just...

41:14.670 --> 41:16.960
It ain't feel right.

41:17.160 --> 41:20.180
Felt like I was running,
you know?

41:20.380 --> 41:21.820
FRANKLIN:
What's it like over there?

41:23.100 --> 41:25.620
That shit was beautiful.

41:25.820 --> 41:27.100
Beautiful.

41:27.300 --> 41:29.590
But hard.

41:30.860 --> 41:33.160
They been through so much.

41:33.360 --> 41:34.770
Colonial rule,

41:34.970 --> 41:36.680
one coup after another.

41:36.880 --> 41:38.580
Warring against they people.

41:38.780 --> 41:40.430
Sounds familiar.

41:40.630 --> 41:44.550
Yeah. But they did
get a new leader.

41:44.750 --> 41:47.470
A man who will do
what needs to get done

41:47.670 --> 41:49.420
to push the country forward.

41:49.620 --> 41:51.470
Even if that means bloodshed.

41:51.670 --> 41:53.610
That's some shit
Avi talked about a lot.

41:53.810 --> 41:56.080
He said the world would have
wiped the Jews out

41:56.280 --> 41:57.950
if they hadn't fought.

41:58.140 --> 42:01.200
Violence as an act of salvation.

42:06.550 --> 42:08.040
What?

42:10.140 --> 42:11.550
Avi's gone.

42:11.740 --> 42:13.840
What you mean, gone?

42:16.700 --> 42:18.320
He's dead?

42:19.570 --> 42:21.710
His warehouse got burned down.

42:22.850 --> 42:24.710
